title: Future Hendrix
body:
Ayvadius DeMun Wilburn (born November 20, 1983), known professionally by his stage name Future, is an American hip hop recording artist.

Born and raised in Atlanta, Georgia, Wilburn first became involved in music as part of the Dungeon Family collective, where he received the nickname the Future.

After amassing a series of mixtapes between 2010 and 2011, Future signed a major-label deal with Epic Records and A1 Recordings, which helped launch Future's own label imprint, Freebandz.

title: Young Thug
body:
Jeffery Lamar Williams (born August 16, 1991), known professionally as Young Thug, is an American rapper from Atlanta, Georgia.

He became known for his commercial debut single Stoner, as well as his collaborations with fellow Southern rappers, such as Rich Homie Quan, Birdman, Waka Flocka Flame, Gucci Mane, Young Scooter, Shy Glizzy, Migos, T.I., and Travi$ Scott.
